race.comment: FORCEFILLY (11) bounced straight back winning comfortably over 1200m at Bathurst. Positioned forward and can do the same here from an inside barrier. Thrown in keeping the 4kg claim, and can get the job done again. CALLENEM THRU (13) was sent out a hot favourite last time and scored by a long neck at this track. Made amends for the narrow first-up defeat at the track and has plenty of scope for improvement. Leading player again. SUPAIRO (7) is in a top Sydney stable and is busting to win. Missed a whisker in a 66 at Muswellbrook last time and is back a touch in grade. NOCTUA (9) deserved her 60 win here and will be fitter again. The wide gate makes it a tougher task today.
